# Node scripts

All build and deploy tooling lives in `scripts/` (Node ≥ 20, ESM). Tests are colocated as `*.test.mjs` next to each module and run via Vitest.

## Run tests after every edit

```pwsh
npx vitest run
```

The husky pre-commit hook runs `npx vitest run`, then `check-tex`, `check-questions`, `check-resources`, and `check-generated`. All must pass to commit.

- If tests **pass**: proceed normally.
- If tests **fail**: stop and report the failures. **Do not modify existing test assertions to make them pass** — test updates require explicit user approval.
- When adding a new pure helper to a tested module, also add a test case (new `describe`/`it` blocks) — don't leave new branches uncovered.

## Module map

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `scripts/deploy-from-overleaf.mjs` | Interactive: clone Overleaf project → `latexmk` both PDFs → place into `public/tex/<sitePath>/{qbt,soln}/` → `clean-tex` → append staging entry |
| `scripts/compile-tex.mjs` | Bulk `latexmk` over a scope (`further-maths` (default) / `tmua` / `all`); `--deploy` copies built PDFs up beside source on success |
| `scripts/check-tex.mjs` | Read-only body-comment hygiene check (rejects full-line comments outside `% ---- Question N ----`). Run by pre-commit and CI. |
| `scripts/clean-tex.mjs` | Strips full-line body comments, collapses long blank runs, re-inserts numbered question delimiters |
| `scripts/check-questions.mjs` | Read-only QBT ⇄ SOLN drift detector. Reports per-question statement diffs, structurally broken pairs (mismatched `% ---- Question N ----` delimiter sets, duplicate delimiters), and per-file integrity issues from `validateBlocks` (missing/extra `\questionitem`, delim-numbering gaps). Wired into `.husky/pre-commit` and `predev`/`prebuild`/`precheck`. Non-zero exit on drift or structural break. |
| `scripts/sync-questions.mjs` | Rewrites SOLN statement regions in place to match QBT. Solution `tcolorbox` content and the `\vspace*{10pt}` prelude are preserved exactly. Skips structurally broken pairs (use `check-questions` to triage; fix delimiter / `\questionitem` mismatches by hand first). |
| `scripts/check-resources.mjs` | Read-only validator for `src/data/resources.ts`. Violations: `missing-file`, `duplicate-id`, `pair-id-unresolved`, `pair-asymmetry`, `pair-type-mismatch`, `pair-topic-mismatch`, `missing-question-count`. Warnings: `orphan-pdf`. Wired into `.husky/pre-commit` only. |
| `scripts/check-generated.mjs` | Read-only verifier that `src/data/{questionCounts,fileHashes}.generated.ts` byte-match what the generators would produce now. Wired into `.husky/pre-commit` only — NOT into `pre*` hooks (those run the generators first; the check would be redundant). |
| `scripts/count-questions.mjs` | npm pre-hook: counts `\questionitem` and writes `src/data/questionCounts.generated.ts`. Pure helpers (`computeQuestionCounts`, `renderQuestionCountsModule`, `GENERATED_PATH`) are exported for `check-generated`. |
| `scripts/hash-assets.mjs` | npm pre-hook: hashes deployed PDFs and writes `src/data/fileHashes.generated.ts`. Pure helpers (`computeFileHashes`, `renderFileHashesModule`, `findPdfFiles`, `GENERATED_PATH`) are exported for `check-generated` / `check-resources`. |
| `scripts/lib/tex-utils.mjs` | `normalizePath`, `shouldProcessTexFile`, `walkTexFiles`, `findDocBoundaries`, `findPackPairs` — shared by check/clean/deploy/sync |
| `scripts/lib/question-blocks.mjs` | Pure parser used by `check-questions` / `sync-questions`: `parseDoc` / `serializeDoc` (CRLF/LF preserving), `splitSolnBlock`, `extractQbtStatement`, `rewriteSolnStatement`, end-to-end `syncPair`, `validateBlocks` (per-file `\questionitem`/delim integrity). Solution boundary = line containing both `\begin{tcolorbox}` and `title={\textbf{Solution}}`. |
| `scripts/lib/site-tree.mjs` | `listTreeShallow`, `pickSitePath` — interactive site-path picker for the deploy script |
| `scripts/lib/resources-derive.mjs` | Regex-based introspection of `src/data/resources.ts` (no full TS parse): `slugify`, `derivePathContext`, `deriveTopicId`, `loadResourcesEntries`, `parseResourcesEntries` (exposes `id`/`file`/`category`/`topic`/`type`/`pairId`) — drives both staging-file derivation and `check-resources`. |
| `scripts/lib/resources-check.mjs` | Pure `checkResources({ entries, diskFiles, deployedPdfs, questionCountKeys }) → { violations, warnings }`. Driven by `scripts/check-resources.mjs`. |
| `scripts/lib/staging.mjs` | `readPending`, `writePendingAtomic`, `addPendingEntry` — reads/merges/writes `data/resources-pending.json` |

## Conventions

- **Pure helpers go in `scripts/lib/`** with a colocated `*.test.mjs`. Keep I/O at the script entry point (`main()`); branchy logic should be importable and testable.
- **Atomic writes** for any file an agent or script consumes: write to `<file>.<rand>.tmp` then `renameSync`. `staging.writePendingAtomic` is the reference pattern — copy it for new staged outputs.
- **No new dependencies without good reason.** The deploy script intentionally inlines a tiny `.env` parser instead of pulling in `dotenv`.
- **`SKIP_TEX_FILES`** in `deploy-from-overleaf.mjs` (`draft.tex`, `original.tex`) lists Overleaf scratch files that should never be picked up as a pack — extend the set rather than adding ad-hoc filtering.

## Database health invariants enforced at pre-commit

The four checks split responsibility cleanly — extend the right one when adding a new invariant:

- **`resources.ts` ↔ filesystem / generated counts** → `check-resources` / `scripts/lib/resources-check.mjs`. Every entry's `file` exists on disk; ids are unique; `pairId` resolves and is symmetric, with partner types `{questions, solutions}` and matching `topic`/`category`; `type:'questions'` `/qbt/` entries are keyed in `questionCounts.generated.ts`. `orphan-pdf` is a warning while the corpus has a known backlog — promote to violation in `resources-check.mjs` once clean.
- **`*.generated.ts` freshness** → `check-generated`. Generated files are byte-identical to what `count-questions` / `hash-assets` would produce now. Always wired pre-commit-only (the `pre*` hooks already run the generators first).
- **In-file QBT/SOLN structural integrity** → `validateBlocks` in `scripts/lib/question-blocks.mjs`, surfaced via `check-questions`. Each question block has exactly one `\questionitem`; delimiter Ns are exactly `1..K`. Fatal kinds contribute to `syncPair`'s `fatal` flag; `extra-questionitem` is non-fatal because the next sync re-derives the statement from QBT.
- **Pair-level QBT ⇄ SOLN parity** → `syncPair` in `scripts/lib/question-blocks.mjs`. Question-number sets are equal; SOLN statement regions match QBT byte-for-byte.

## Deploy workflow contract

`deploy-from-overleaf.mjs` is the one workflow that mutates many parts of the repo at once. Hold its invariants when editing it:

1. **One project per topic** is the modern convention; the legacy two-project fallback (separate QBT + Solns Overleaf projects) must keep working — `findPackTex` handles single-`.tex` projects with unambiguous classification (`[Solns]` ⇒ soln, `(QBT) ` ⇒ qbt).
2. **Site-path picker** is the only way to choose a deploy directory — don't add a freehand path flag without good reason. The tex root itself can never be the deploy target.
3. **Staging entries** (`data/resources-pending.json`) are append-or-replace by `id`. Re-deploys must prompt for overwrite confirmation. Schema is documented in `data/README.md` — bump `schemaVersion` in lockstep with any field change and update the README.
4. **The deploy script must not edit `src/data/resources.ts`.** That's the splicer agent's job. The staging file is the only hand-off.
5. **`OVERLEAF_GIT_TOKEN`** is read from `.env` at the repo root via the inline loader. Never log it.

If you change any of these, update both `AGENTS.md` (Workflows section) and `data/README.md`.
